<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F22FEAD48A75147FE2BFF5F" lastPageId="365" lastPageNumber="366" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F22FEAC48A75147FE6AF81C" blockId="364.[151,1437,1643,2028]" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F22FEAC48A75147FE01F974" bold="true" box="[151,420,1643,1668]" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F22FEAC4A455140FD68F973" box="[629,717,1644,1668]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="364" pageNumber="365" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Testaceous-ferruginous, except petiole black, antennal segment 8 testaceous and antennal segments 9–10 whitish. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 10:6:15:8:6:6:5.5:5:5:8.5. Head very excavated, shiny, smooth, unsculptured; frontal line absent; occipital carina absent; temple absent; POL = 0.3; OL = 3; OOL = 6. Palpal formula 3/2. Pronotum crossed by strong transverse impression, shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Scutum shiny, smooth, unsculptured, with some transverse keels on lateral regions. Metanotum flat, transversely striate, with two lateral pointed apophyses (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F22FEAC4C445033FB48F8C7" box="[1140,1261,1823,1847]" captionStart="PLATE 111" captionStartId="363.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1410,244,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-76@363.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="363" captionText="PLATE 111. A, B. Male genitalia. C. Scutum + metathorax + propodeum. D. Chela. A. Gonatopus nearcticus, from Greece. B. G. nigricans, from Malaya. Different shapes of dorsal process of paramere. C, D. G. bicuspis, holotype (from Olmi 1993d). Scale bar 0.14 mm for A and B, 0.40 mm for C and 0.12 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278764/files/figure.png" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Plate 111C</figureCitation>
). Metathorax + propodeum shiny, smooth, unsculptured; posterior surface of propodeum transversely striate. Mesopleuron and metapleuron transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture distinct and complete. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 13:3:4.5:15.5:25. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F22FEAC4A8250A0FC97F854" box="[690,818,1932,1956]" captionStart="PLATE 111" captionStartId="363.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1410,244,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-76@363.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="363" captionText="PLATE 111. A, B. Male genitalia. C. Scutum + metathorax + propodeum. D. Chela. A. Gonatopus nearcticus, from Greece. B. G. nigricans, from Malaya. Different shapes of dorsal process of paramere. C, D. G. bicuspis, holotype (from Olmi 1993d). Scale bar 0.14 mm for A and B, 0.40 mm for C and 0.12 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278764/files/figure.png" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Plate 111D</figureCitation>
) with one large subapical tooth and one row of six lamellae + one bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F22FEAC4A96509CFC84F838" box="[678,801,1968,1992]" captionStart="PLATE 111" captionStartId="363.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1410,244,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-76@363.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="363" captionText="PLATE 111. A, B. Male genitalia. C. Scutum + metathorax + propodeum. D. Chela. A. Gonatopus nearcticus, from Greece. B. G. nigricans, from Malaya. Different shapes of dorsal process of paramere. C, D. G. bicuspis, holotype (from Olmi 1993d). Scale bar 0.14 mm for A and B, 0.40 mm for C and 0.12 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278764/files/figure.png" pageId="364" pageNumber="365">Plate 111D</figureCitation>
) with two rows of 16 lamellae; distal apex with about 16 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F23FEAD48F757B4FE2BFF5F" blockId="365.[199,1317,151,284]" box="[199,398,151,176]" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F23FEAD48F757B4FEAEFF40" bold="true" box="[199,267,152,176]" pageId="365" pageNumber="366">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
